Noticed five belly-up ~16" cisco between Country Club and Jossart Island. Later reports of "a hundred" dead cisco in this region. None noticed in Lake Kawaguesaga an hour later.

column1: This last set of 2016 samples that began in April represent a decadal "snapshot" of QW status of lake Minocqua. The last detailed Minocqua Deep Hole monitoring (in addition to the LTT monitoring by DNR that was taken over by John Gray and Regis in 2016) was by USGS in 2005-07.

The Minocqua/Kawaguesaga Lakes Preservation Association is to be commended for funding most of the 2016 sample analyses (those in addition to standard CLMN monitoring in Lakes Minocqua and Kawaguesaga).
